{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place 120 g sparkling wine, 300 g orange juice and sugar in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>8 min\/100°C\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add remaining 300 g orange juice and mix <nobr>3 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer mixture up to 4 cm deep into freezable containers (e.g. aluminium, silicone) and cover with cling film. Cool mixture completely before freezing for at least 8 hours.","Cut frozen mixture into pieces (approx. 4 cm x 4 cm) with a long sharp knife. Place pieces in mixing bowl and crush with aid of spatula <nobr>30 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to wine glasses or champagne flutes and pour the remaining 630 g sparkling wine over the sorbet. Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["750 g sparkling wine","600 g orange juice, freshly squeezed (7-9 oranges)","150 g sugar"]}],"id":"r127645","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-iTs75JuCidQ\/XZXYrIXM_cI\/AAAAAAAAgAo\/D4oizWL_S8ooSr3aGFeBIvBav8l-QheuwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RMUgjWcrytBu7rHt.png","title":"Orange Sorbet with Sparkling Wine","publishedAt":"2016-11-07T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 glass","carbohydrates":"30 g","calories":"777 kJ \/ 186 kcal"},"usefulItems":"freezable containers (e.g. aluminium, silicone), cling film, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["For a non-alcoholic version replace the sparkling wine with sparkling water.","Replace the orange juice with another citrus juice (e.g. lemon, tangerine, grapefruit)."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","8h","8 glasses"]}